weight loss dieting and breastfeeding im breastfeeding my baby and wondering what is the best way to get in shape and lose some lbs while still being able to feed my baby breastmilk i wanna lose about lbs non pregnancy weight there's not a magic bullet for this you don't want to diet heavily you need to eat a well balanced sufficient diet to ensure you will stay healthy your baby will get what it needs regardless but you have to take care of yourself you can exercise eat well and live a healthy lifestyle you can also do weight watchers but you have to add points to the program to compensate for breastfeeding for some women breastfeeding will do it i lost lbs eating more than usual just from the constant caloric drain from breasfeeding for others breastfeeding makes them retain weight no matter which is you you can't expect fast results good luck and keep on nursing that's what's most important Breastfeeding Dieting Folic acid Weight Watchers Anorexia nervosa Atkins Nutritional Approach Obesity Childbirth Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Low-carbohydrate diet Breast Brassiere Diabetes mellitus Binge eating disorder Weight loss Weight training Pregnancy Sesame Street Coeliac disease Fertility awareness Bodybuilding Nutrition Vegetarianism Adjustable gastric band Infant Raw food diet Urinary incontinence Terri Schiavo Cancer Milk Nipple piercing International Code of Marketing of Breast-milk Substitutes Weight Prostate cancer Omega-3 fatty acid Obstetrics Super Size Me Midwifery Tocopherol Breast milk Guinea pig Inheritance (computer science) Fancy rat Calorie restriction Domestic rabbit Healthy eating Chocolate Human height Stomach cancer Parenting The Care Bears (television series) Health insurance Multiple sclerosis Beetle Protein-energy malnutrition Nipple Explosive material Pound Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Hamster Domestic goat Insulin Clinical depression Whitney Houston Hypertension Sea-Monkey Internal ballistics Baby bottle Abortion debate Fasting Handloading Med